frozen VF `content/manuscript-Gide.qmd` into English as the new
`content/manuscript.qmd`. Machine-performed, style-anchored on the author's
pre-AI-era English prose; the editorial brief and prose ratchet apply to
the output, not assumed from the French.

## Relevant files
- `content/manuscript-Gide.qmd` — VF source (frozen: HAL/tag `gide-submitted-2026-06-29`)
- `~/CNRS/html/src/Ha-Duong.bib` — list of the author's publications (style anchor source)
- `docs/editorial-brief.md` — standing decisions the translation must satisfy

## Actions
1. Assemble the style anchor: select 3–5 pre-AI-era English articles
   (first-authored, prose-rich), extract representative passages.
   **Author validates the selection before translation starts.**
2. Translate section by section, prompting with the anchor.

